  "text": "In Figure 10 , the self-excited thermoacoustic oscillations are compared in terms of their RMS values and in terms of the maximal fluctuation of the global heat release rate. The bifurcation parameter is the plenum length, as shown in Figures 1, 8 and 9 . At each length investigated, a self-excited oscillation was calculated with all optimal ANNs for 50 . As discussed by Jaensch et al., [CITATION_1] the thermoacoustic oscillations of the present configurations hardly depend on the initial condition used. In order to minimize the computational effort of the CFD simulation the simulation, was started from a perturbed case. This situation cannot be reproduced with the ANNs. Therefore, we focus the discussion on comparing the fully developed thermoacoustic oscillation. For the results shown in Figure  10 , only the last 20 of the 50 time series are used.",
